al"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/02 4:23:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lady Vox and Lord Nagafen</span><hr size=1> ...only go on vox/naggy raids with people who know what they are doing. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Honestly, that's the biggest key to having a good raid.  At level 45, even with GOOD resist gear AND buffs, the AE is gonna eat you up, and the fear will send you running, but it'll still be a fun fight for ya. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Other things you could do include looking at the maps of perma and sol b so you know where you are/should be (and don't end up in the bear pits in perma, etc), making sure you have the appropriate resist gear and shammy potions, etc.<br><br>Naggy raids were always a LOT of fun; Vox was a pain in the rear due to the Cheals.  I miss both of em a lot.<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=