thebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lady Vox and Lord Nagafen</span><hr size=1> Hi again-<br><br>Actually, the key to killing either of them FAST with few players is:<br>a). getting in some good resistance debuffs.<br>b). having enough wizzies/mages/druids who are willing to bind rush them and nuke their tuschies off.<br><br>With only 32k hp, both these mobs are VERY susceptable to things like ice comet/concussion/repeat (~1kdmg/full hit).  With the level limit and the dragon-resist fear, having pure melee try to kill them (esp vox with her @$%#$% cheals) can be a real pain.<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaldraith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdraith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 5:19:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Vox/Nagafen</span><hr size=1> I participated in 8 sucessful Vox raids, 2 succesful Naggy raids and 2 unsuccessful Naggy raids before I turned 53.  These were raids with people from 4 or 5 guilds, all regular attendees to the raids and therefore experienced dragon killers.  Recently I've been attending dragons raids again with one of my alts (level 45 druid), so far 65 Naggy and 4 Vox, all successful and for the most part guild-only (mostly alts, with 2 or 3 mains that are still under 52).<br><br>The advice above is very good, and the most important piece of advice is that whoever is in charge really needs to know what they're doing, and people participating have to be good at foloowing instructions.  If not, chances are the raid will fail, no matter how many people you throw at the dragon.<br><br>With my main, raids ranged in numbers from 24 to 40 people.  This was a while ago, with no high-level buffs available, no epics and much lower quality of weapons and resist gear than currently available.  Our raids now are much smaller.  Our record is killing Nagafen with 12 people (of which only 1 was a cleric) and Vox with 16 (although only a rogue and a shaman were left standing at the end).  Vox is significantly harder than Nagafen since due to her Complete Heals you need enchanter sieves, and even then she might still CH a couple of times.  Still doable without enchanters, but much tougher.  The only time I was in a raid with no enchanters there were 36 people and only 18 survived, after 4 CHs.  The lower numbers are a reflection of higher damage weapons (e.g. we have a rogue with Ragebringer and en epic monk now in the dragon crew), better buffs (Focus, Shissar, etc), and more experience/better tactics (in-guild group that knows what they're doing).<br><br>Assuming the raids you attend have good leadership, make sure you have good resist gear.  Make an investment in some diamond and blue diamond jewelry. If that is out of your price range, there are still some good things you can get cheaply, such as a rune boned fork, cloak of the icebear, earrings of fire reflection, etc.  There are some good guides to resist gear on the web, you just need to do a bit of research.  My level 45 druid has attended all of his killings with about 120 MR and 120 FR buffed.  That has been enough to resist most of the Fears, although the fire/cold AE really eat him up.  If you can get to 100 unbuffed in MR and CR/FR, then you should be OK at level 45.<br><br>Some other tips:<br>- We find that shadowknights make the best Naggy/Vox tanks.  They can taunt with spells and keep the dragon on one target, making healing easier. Warriors can't taunt them since they are red to a level 52.<br>- When you are low on clerics, paladins work great.  Whenever we've killed a dragon with 1 only 1 cleric we've had 2 or 3 paladins.  LoH is great for this kind of fight.<br>- Positioning is very important.  The main tank needs to know how to do this.<br><br>Hope you get to do this, it's a lot of fun!<br><br>Galdraith<br>Warder of the Corps<br>Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaldraith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdraith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 5:22:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Vox/Nagafen</span><hr size=1> One last thing.  Although wizards are nice to have and help a lot, they are definitely not necessary.  In our recent old-world dragon slayings the most wizards we've had has been 1, and in at least half of the fights we had none, making it a pure melee fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uturomtoesmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turom Toesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/24/02 11:26:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fraglak.com/images/sig/turom_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Vox/Nagafen</span><hr size=1> As far as I'm concerned, INT casters are a bit of a waste on Nags.  Chanters are the only INT casters you really need for Vox.<br><br>Rogues and